  <question type="stack">
    <name>
      <text>Free-text with final answer (calculus)</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<div class="stack-comment">
<h2>Free-text input</h2>This question asks students to type in their complete answer using free-text input.  Instructions on how to do this are below.  The final answer will automatically be extracted and assessed with a normal STACK question.  Free-text can also be used with manual grading, or combined with other input types, as needed.
</div>
<p>Let \(f'(x)= {@dq1@}\). Given that \(f({@x0@})={@f0@}\), find \(f(x)\).</p>
<p>Work line by line below, justifying your answer fully.  Your last line should be your answer \(f(x)=...\).</p>
<div class="free-text-container">
[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]
[[ascii input="ans1"]]
  [[extractor targetinput="ans2" type="lastexpr"/]]
[[/ascii]]
</div>
<p>[[hint title="Input help"]][[commonstring key="free_text_fact"/]][[/hint]]</p>
<p style="display:none">[[input:ans2]]</p>
<p>[[validation:ans2]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text>[[ascii]]{@ta1@}[[/ascii]]</text>
    </generalfeedback>
    <defaultgrade>2</defaultgrade>
